emotes.msg: Double-click on me to hear what I have to say.
Help! Stop thief!
My bellows! Thank you. Take this, with my thanks!
Furthermore, I believe you have proven yourself worthy of a weapons upgrade. This Oil of Rendering will help you achieve one.
OilGiven

Now you should visit the Quartermaster's workshop and buy one of his Training Weapons. They will serve you well in your initial travels, and if you use this special oil on them,I guarantee you will enhance it.

The Quartermaster has locked himself away in his shop for some reason--he must be feeling shy today. Little does he know that I smithed a copy to his key, which I will give to you! You'll find his workshop across the courtyard from where you first entered.
Good luck!
The Academy Blacksmith grins wryly.
Those Sparring Golems are pretty exciting, aren't they? Thanks for the token--I'll return it to the Practice Area for you.
I am a Blacksmith --not a Scribe.
The Academy Foreman would be happy to see this--he's been plagued by these pests for ever so long. Maybe he should take a shower!
No, friend--I must give this to you as a gesture of my friendship. Now I can get back to work! Use this oil on one of the Quartermaster's items--you won't be dissatisfied with the result!
No thanks. I am far too busy to read these days.
No thanks. I am far too busy to read these days.
This is one of the Training items forged by our Quartermaster. If you use the Oil of Rendering that I gave you on it, you'll find its powers will increase tremendously.

This is the key to the Quartermaster's workshop. You should pay him a visit! To unlock the door, double-click on the key, then double-click on the door.
RecruitSent
The Blacksmith looks worried and tired.

The Queen and her advisors were correct. The Nexus towns are still under threat. I can only hope that our recent efforts to fortify this area will withstand the assault. Go to the Senior Guard--he will know what's best at this time.
Ah! The Academy Foreman must have sent you over to me. He's always had a good eye for capable folk.
OilGiven

Thank you so much for helping me with those incorrible Mosswarts! Now use the key I gave you to unlock the door to the Quartermaster's workshop. You'll find his workshop across the courtyard from where you first entered. He's selling items that you'll be able to upgrade by pouring the Oil of Rendering on it.
WaspWingGiven

Perhaps you could help me with these thieving Mosswarts. They and their noxious kin have stolen my bellows! How can I contribute to building these fortifications if I do not have them? The last time I saw them, they were running towards the vegetable gardens. Retrieve my bellows for me, and I will reward you!

Wonderful! A new arrival! You should visit the Academy Foreman--he's been having a world of trouble with the Carpenter Wasps over in his construction area. He's nearly at his wit's end...and will be glad to see you.
